\pard\sb320\sa200\f0\fs32\b\cf1 Task 10 -- Writeup\b0\cf0\par
\pard\sa160\f0\fs22 Steps:\par
\pard\li480\fi-240\f0\fs22 1.\tab Update README.md with the final results (metrics table) and clear steps to reproduce the pipeline end to end.\par
\pard\li480\fi-240\f0\fs22 2.\tab Do a final review pass over the whole pipeline, not just your own part -- use the review skill.\par
\pard\li480\fi-240\f0\fs22 3.\tab Add the closing entry to journal/agent-journal.md summarising the project.\par
\pard\sb320\sa200\f0\fs32\b\cf1 Task 11 -- Stretch (optional): Streamlit app\b0\cf0\par
\pard\sa160\f0\fs22 Only if time allows. Full design is in spec/01-system-architecture.md -- read that first. The short version: load Paul's saved model_pipeline.joblib once, reuse Mercy's cleaning function directly rather than re-implementing it, and support both a single-customer form and a batch CSV upload through the same code path.\par
\pard\sa40\sb80\li360\f1\fs19\cf1\b CODE HINT\b0\cf0\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19 import streamlit as st\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19 import joblib\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19 import pandas as pd\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19 from src.data.cleaning import clean_raw\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19 \par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19 @st.cache_resource\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19 def load_pipeline():\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19     return joblib.load('models/model_pipeline.joblib')\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19 \par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19 pipeline = load_pipeline()\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19 \par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19 with st.form('customer'):\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19     tenure = st.number_input('Tenure (months)', 0, 72, 12)\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19     contract = st.selectbox(\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19         'Contract', ['Month-to-month', 'One year', 'Two year'])\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19     # ... remaining fields, one widget per raw column\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19     submitted = st.form_submit_button('Predict')\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19 \par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19 if submitted:\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19     raw = pd.DataFrame([\{'tenure': tenure, 'Contract': contract, ...\}])\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19     cleaned = clean_raw(raw)\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19     proba = pipeline.predict_proba(cleaned)[0, 1]\par
\pard\li360\sa20\f1\fs19     st.metric('Churn probability', f'\{proba:.0%\}')\par
\pard\sa160\f0\fs22\par
\pard\sa160\f0\fs22 Deploy via Streamlit Community Cloud: push to GitHub, connect the repo at share.streamlit.io, point it at src/app/streamlit_app.py.\par
\pard\sb320\sa200\f0\fs32\b\cf1 Deliverable\b0\cf0\par
